<li id="cite_note-7"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-7">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Ojeda Reyes, Félix, <i>El Desterrado de París</i>, p. 8. Betances is quoted as saying once that he never saw his mother go to any religious service, and that when his father took him to church, he would stand in the back, close to the door, and not pay much attention to <a href="/wiki/Mass_(liturgy)" title="Mass (liturgy)">Mass</a>.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-8"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-8">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Ojeda Reyes, Félix, <i>El Desterrado de París</i>, pp. 8, 17–19</span></li>
